/-- **Quantitative large-prime-factor corollary from `MainInputs`.**

This is the assembly-facing form of `prop:large-prime-factor`: the dyadic
reciprocal summation is discharged inside `Applications`, so no separate
reciprocal-envelope hypothesis appears here. -/
theorem large_prime_factor (H : MainInputs) :
    ∃ c > (0 : ℝ), ∃ C > (0 : ℝ), ∀ N Y : ℕ, 3 ≤ Y → Y ≤ N →
      (exceptionalGtYCount N Y : ℝ)
        ≤ C * (N : ℝ) * (1 + Real.log N) * saving c Y :=
