/-- Fixed-power specialization of `prop:large-prime-factor` from `MainInputs`.

This is the assembly-facing form of the manuscript's first displayed
specialization: once `Y ≥ N^η`, the logarithmic prefactor in the large-prime
factor estimate is absorbed into the saving at level `N`. -/
theorem large_prime_factor_power_threshold (H : MainInputs) {η : ℝ} (hη : 0 < η) :
    ∃ c > (0 : ℝ), ∃ C > (0 : ℝ), ∀ N Y : ℕ, 3 ≤ N → 3 ≤ Y → Y ≤ N →
      (N : ℝ) ^ η ≤ (Y : ℝ) →
      (exceptionalGtYCount N Y : ℝ) ≤ C * (N : ℝ) * saving c N :=
