the `9/16` logarithmic saving. -/
theorem large_prime_factor_exp_log_threshold (H : MainInputs) :
    ∃ c > (0 : ℝ), ∃ C > (0 : ℝ), ∀ N Y : ℕ, 3 ≤ N → 3 ≤ Y → Y ≤ N →
      Real.exp ((Real.log (N : ℝ)) ^ ((3 : ℝ) / 4)) ≤ (Y : ℝ) →
      (exceptionalGtYCount N Y : ℝ) ≤ C * (N : ℝ) * savingNineSixteen c N :=
  exceptionalGtY_exp_log_threshold_of_main (erdos_straus_main H)

/-- **Clean prime-counting form of `cor:prime-exceptional`.**

This carries the stronger Applications-level statement through the main theorem:
